entions"},{"source":"recHSmQEKntpgnVpS","target":"recRiyMlpGQNCIZvm","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"reczeShNAHRYs1di1","ref":"1Kgs.19.1","text":"And Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and withal how he had slain all the prophets with the sword.","year":-906},{"id":"recJx17a7E4aX9h0e","ref":"1Kgs.19.2","text":"Then Jezebel sent a messenger unto Elijah, saying, So let the gods do to me, and more also, if I make not thy life as the life of one of them by to morrow about this time.","year":-906},{"id":"recUsCeqzuv4fAeRS","ref":"1Kgs.19.3","text":"And when he saw that, he arose, and went for his life, and came to Beersheba, which belongeth to Judah, and left his servant there.","year":-906},{"id":"reclIkilq0mwkSIzb","ref":"1Kgs.19.4","text":"But he himself went a day’s journey into the wilderness, and came and sat down under a juniper tree: and he requested for himself that he might die; and said, It is enough; now, O LORD, take away my life; for I am not better than my fathers.","year":-906},{"id":"rectNPydLYzX6zXYW","ref":"1Kgs.19.5","text":"And as he lay and slept under a juniper tree, behold, then an angel touched him, and said unto him, Arise and eat.","year":-906},{"id":"rec3s8FMSjlLUq34U","ref":"1Kgs.19.6","text":"And he looked, and, behold, there was a cake baken on the coals, and a cruse of water at his head. And he did eat and drink, and laid him down again.","year":-906},{"id":"recKtFm032yQDKXhS","ref":"1Kgs.19.7","text":"And the angel of the LORD came again the second time, and touched him, and said, Arise and eat; because the journey is too great for thee.","year":-906},{"id":"rec3or1Z7bWVigsdZ","ref":"1Kgs.19.8","text":"And he arose, and did eat and drink, and went in the strength of that meat forty days and forty nights unto Horeb the mount of God.","year":-906}]}
